<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-26T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-26T09:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.5151/434: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cox</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-26T10:00:00-04:00">April 26, 1935—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>33. I conveyed substance of Department’s telegram No. 36, April 25, 11
                            a.m., to the Minister for Foreign Affairs yesterday evening at the same
                            time leaving a memorandum with him outlining representations made. The
                            Minister stated that he would endeavor at once to expedite a response
                            from the Ministry of Finance.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cox</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>